commitResults.messageTitle: Finish level 1: Greet, Echo, Exit Duke bot can repeat what a user says
added an abstract class named "task", which all tasks will inherit from
Level 2: Added the ability to store whatever text entered by the user in DUKE
Renamed Task to Manager Echo to Echo Manager and changed some variable names to better represent the system I am modelling
Implemented a class named task, which is the user's task, and ensure that it still works with task 2
Task 3: implemented the requirements for task 3 using task manager and task
Added Deadline, which is an extension of Task
Added Todo, which is another extension of Task
Added Event, which is yet another extension of Task
Task 4: added support for todo, event and deadlines
implemented some exceptions for event, todo and deadline to deal with inaccurate user input
shifted the handling of "done" related user input to ListManager, handled exception that can arise from the user during the "done" operation
changed the number of "__" to match that of the cs2103t project website
updated test that will test the todo, event and deadline features and well as how exception related to these features wills be handled
Task 4 completed - able to handle all possible errors in the current version of duke
Add deletion feature for Duke
commitResults.messageBody: can delete tasks in the list using the command "delete x", where x is a number representing a task in the list

commitResults.messageTitle: updated test to test the deletion feature
Add 2 boolean function, checkStringStartingEquals and checkStringEquals, to check userInput.
commitResults.messageBody:
checkStringStartingEqual checks if the first n characters of String is equal to a given String
checkStringEquals checks if the user input is equal to a given String or equal to a given String + " "
This is to avoid repetitive and messy code.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update automated text ui files
Improved the handling of user input
commitResults.messageBody:
Moved the handling of user input from Duke to ListManager using a new method, handleAllUserInput
Added the padSpaces method to Manager abstract class to help the generating to Strings

commitResults.messageTitle: Catch exception where user does not put a space after a task. eg "todosleep"
Level 7 - Save tasks onto hard disk
commitResults.messageBody:
Changed Task, Todo, Event, Deadline to allow these classes to output the format to be saved in the datafile, and create tasks from parsed input from the datafile

Added feature that will create data folder and dukedata.txt if they dont exist

Added feature that will save the tasks in the datafile automatically when the task list changes

Added feature that will load data from the datafile, restore the state of the task list in the previous session

commitResults.messageTitle: Change default input in dukedata.txt for testing purposes
Update testing files to ensure previous features are not lost
Level 8 - added date and time handling for deadline tasks, in the dd-mm-yyyy format
Add support for deadline dates of the format yyyy-mm-dd
Level 8 - Merged the save feature from level 7 with the date feature of level 8
commitResults.messageBody:
Rectified the Deadline class such that it handles dates properly when loading saved data
Handled exception in ListManager and Duke where the dukedata is not in the correct format for it to become a task
